data.title: Victoria Prince: The beloved wife of Kevin Federline

data.text:
Victoria is Kevin Federline’s wife and married for over a decade. They first met in 2008 at a bowling league and fell in love with each other. They delivered their daughter, their first child named ‘Jordan Kay’. Later they got married in 2013 throwing a surprise wedding ceremony in Las Vegas. Peyton Marie, their second daughter was born in 2014. Kevin loves his wife and mentioned her in his Twitter handle as his glue, foundation and the rarest gem. He also claims to have learn a lot from this relationship and loves her all the more. He was married between 2004 and 2007 to Britney Spears, the popular pop star.

She along with her husband is getting ready to shift from Los Angeles to Hawaii with their daughters along with Jayden and Preston. According to Federline’s attorney, the family is moving to Hawaii to escape LA microscope.

Former volleyball player

Victoria had an active sports life and an impressive resume to boast about. Hailing from Washington, she played varsity volleyball in high school for three years before completing her college. Before transferring to Manoa’s Hawaii University, Victoria Prince joined Washington State University. Here, she was part of AVCA All-American team. In 2006, she graduated and competed against Olympians Misty May-Treanor and Kerri Walsh.

Entrepreneur and School teacher

She graduated in Speech from Hawaii University. She is an entrepreneur and special education teacher. In 2017, she co-founded ‘School Box Club’, which is now defunct. Being a mother, she had to buy workbooks, crayons, paper and pens, etc. for her children. She wanted an easy way to shop for such items that encouraging her to set up this business.
